table.body:
HM Revenue & Customs (HMRC) will tell you their decision in writing - along with how much you must pay or be repaid.

If you disagree with the appeal decision, you can either:

- ask HMRC to [review their decision](http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/complaints-appeals/how-to-appeal/indirect-tax.htm#2 "How to ask HMRC to review one of their decisions"){:rel="external"}
- appeal to the independent [tax tribunal](http://www.justice.gov.uk/tribunals/tax/appeals "Appealing to the tax tribunal"){:rel="external"}

*[HMRC]: HM Revenue & Customs
